name: Ravindra Pratap Singh
position: Tehsildar and Executive Magistrate, Govt of Rajasthan | Entrepreneur | Career Counselor | Founder & MD | Mentor | Political Consultant
about:
I've worn many hats in my career- Director, Writer, Business Analyst, BDM, Marketer and Strategist. As a result, I have a unique ability to manage multi-disciplinary projects and to navigate complex challenges. But actual experience has taught me that my professional value boils down to the following:

-I am a Young Entrepreneur and Work on 4 Major Part:- Improve Profitability, Increase Capacity, Improve Cash Flow & Develop Sustainability.
Understanding means fewer missteps, and missteps cost a fortune.

-I don't care who gets credit. I just want to win.

-I have Big Ideas.

-Lots of people have Big ideas. Execution is what matters, and I do execution.

-If my left and right brain were hands, I'd be ambidextrous.

-I'm the calm one.

-I run toward fires.

recommendations: ["Priyanka Biswas “I had the pleasure of graduating from IIT Bombay with Ravindra and working alongside him at our first startup job. From the very beginning, it was clear that Ravindra possesses exceptional leadership qualities that set him apart. His entrepreneurial spirit and sharp management skills have consistently been his strongest assets, making him a true force in any business environment. Ravindra's ability to navigate challenges, inspire teams, and drive results is truly commendable. As a founder of multiple companies, he has repeatedly demonstrated his ability to take ideas from concept to execution, while maintaining a clear vision and delivering impressive results. His strategic mindset, combined with his knack for making sound decisions under pressure, ensures that any company would benefit immensely from having him in a leadership role. I highly recommend Ravindra for any organization looking for a visionary leader and an outstanding entrepreneur. He will undoubtedly be an asset to any team he joins.”","Shreya Ghosh “I had the pleasure of working closely with Ravindra at IPAC. His analytical acumen has been a critical asset in optimizing our operations and ensuring we stay ahead of the curve. In field management, Ravindra excels at leading teams with precision and effectiveness. He knows how to motivate his team, ensuring everyone is aligned with the project’s goals and delivering results. His operational skills are equally impressive—he manages processes seamlessly, ensuring everything runs smoothly and efficiently. Ravindra’s team management skills are second to none. He understands how to bring out the best in his team members, fostering a collaborative environment where everyone feels valued and empowered to contribute. His leadership style is both inspiring and inclusive, making him a natural leader who others look up to. He has a unique ability to connect with stakeholders at all levels, building strong relationships crucial for any project's success. Many of us have learned from his approach to managing these relationships, and his influence has made a lasting impact on our professional development. Ravindra is not just a manager; he is a leader who leads by example. His dedication, strategic thinking, and ability to navigate complex challenges make him an invaluable asset to any team. I highly recommend Ravindra for any leadership role—he is a true professional who consistently delivers excellence.”"]

about:
🔰Project Manager | 🎯 Certified ScrumMaster (CSM) | 🚀 Driving Excellence in Project Execution and Agile Leadership

✅ Results-driven professional with a proven track record in delivering complex projects seamlessly and aligning outcomes with organizational goals. I bring expertise across diverse domains, blending technical proficiency with strategic project governance to achieve excellence.

✳️ Core Competencies:
🔹 Project Management & Governance: Skilled in end-to-end project lifecycles, resource allocation, and risk management.
🔹 Agile Expertise: Certified ScrumMaster (CSM), championing agile practices to enhance team performance and project delivery.
🔹 ITIL & Cloud IT Proficiency: Experienced in ITIL best practices for application stability and adept at leveraging cloud technologies to optimize infrastructure.
🔹 Supply Chain & Operations: Passionate about optimizing global operations and ensuring efficient processes in Supply Chain Management.
🔹 Stakeholder Engagement: Strong communication and collaboration skills, fostering relationships and driving successful outcomes with cross-functional teams.
🔹 Leadership & Process Improvement: Proven ability to lead teams, identify process enhancements, and implement strategies for operational efficiency.

💡 Key Achievements:
✅ Successfully managed large-scale operations and projects for Mega and Large-cap clients, delivering measurable results.
✅ Expertise in New Product Introduction (NPI), New Product Development (NPD), and Cross-Functional Team coordination.
✅ Enhanced organizational performance through strategic Customer Relationship and Service Management.

📌 What Drives Me:
🚀 Passionate about merging project management principles with IT innovation to achieve outstanding business outcomes.
🕵️‍♂️ With an analytical mindset and collaborative approach, I thrive in dynamic environments, ensuring seamless execution and continuous improvement.

🤝 Let’s Connect:
I am eager to explore opportunities to contribute my expertise in Project Management, IT, and Supply Chain. Together, we can drive innovation and achieve remarkable growth.

📩 Reach out to discuss synergies or explore potential collaborations!

        Show more

          
    
  
      

        
          The American Society of Mechanical Engineers (ASME) is a professional association that, in its own words, "promotes the art, science, and practice of multidisciplinary engineering and allied sciences around the globe" via "continuing education, training and professional development, codes and standards, research, conferences and publications, government relations, and other forms of outreach."ASME is thus an engineering society, a standards organization, a research and development organization, an advocacy organization, a provider of training and education, and a nonprofit organization. Founded as an engineering society focused on mechanical engineering in North America, ASME is today multidisciplinary and global.

          ASME is introducing a new program for engineering students, ASME EFx, which is an offshoot of the Society’s successful ASME Engineering Festival (ASME E-Fest) program. The new ASME EFx events, the first of which is planned to be held in India next month, have been conceived as smaller-scale versions of the ASME E-Fests that can be easily staged by local colleges and universities throughout the world.The new ASME EFx events, which are intended to accommodate up to several hundred attendees and last one day or less, offer colleges and universities a novel way to engage with their students, provide students with professional development and skills training, and prepare them to compete at full ASME E-Fests. Planned and administered by local organizers with the assistance of ASME staff, the new events give students a taste of the ASME E-Fests experience without the costs associated with traveling to and attending a regular ASME E-Fest.

publications: [{"title":"How Many Stocks for Maximizing Risk-Adjusted Return? Perspective from Indian Stock Market","subtitle":"Journal of Insurance and Financial Management","date":"July 24, 2022","description":"Portfolio managers and investors alike continuously grapple with trying to outperform the benchmarks, while keeping in mind the right number of stocks in the portfolio for optimal diversification. Through our analysis of the Indian stock market, we show that by random selection of stocks, the odds of outperforming the index are very low. Instead, if investors incorporate the ‘quality’ factor in stock selection, the probability of outperforming the index improves substantially and is statistically significant - at around 5% outperformance per annum at 90% confidence.By incorporating the quality factor, they can own a fairly small basket of 15 to 25 stocks, which captures 90% of the benefit of owning the benchmark at 90% confidence and generates strong outperformance compared to the index. This is much lower than the 45 stocks required for reducing only the diversifiable risk by 90% with a 90% confidence, as the previous studies suggest. These could serve as practical guidelines for portfolio construction and improving returns."}]

publications: [{"title":"Analysing the Extent of Misinformation in Cancer Related Tweets","subtitle":"International AAAI Conference on Web and Social Media (ICWSM 2020)","date":"Mar 2020","description":"Twitter has become one of the most sought after places to discuss a wide variety of topics, including medically relevant issues such as cancer. This helps spread awareness regarding the various causes, cures and prevention methods of cancer. However, no proper analysis has been performed, which discusses the validity of such claims. In this work, we aim to tackle the misinformation spread in such platforms. We collect and present a dataset regarding tweets which talk specifically about cancer and propose an attention-based deep learning model for automated detection of misinformation along with its spread. We then do a comparative analysis of the linguistic variation in the text corresponding to misinformation and truth. This analysis helps us gather relevant insights on various social aspects related to misinformed tweets."},{"title":"Performance statistics and learning based detection of exploitative speculative attacks","subtitle":"16th ACM International Conference on Computing Frontiers","date":"May 2019","description":"Most of the modern processors perform out-of-order speculative executions to maximise system performance. Spectre and Meltdown exploit these optimisations and execute certain instructions leading to leakage of confidential information of the victim. All the variants of this class of attacks necessarily exploit branch prediction or speculative execution. Using this insight, we develop a two-step strategy to effectively detect these attacks using performance counter statistics, correlation coefficient model, deep neural network and fast Fourier transform. Our approach is expected to provide reliable, fast and highly accurate results with no perceivable loss in system performance or system overhead."},{"title":"RATAFIA: Ransomware Analysis using Time And Frequency Informed Autoencoders","subtitle":"IEEE International Symposium on Hardware Oriented Security and Trust (HOST)","date":"Jan 2019","description":"Ransomware can produce direct and controllable economic loss, which makes it one of the most prominent threats in cyber security. As per the latest statistics, more than half of malwares reported in Q1 of 2017 are ransomwares and there is a potent threat of a novice cybercriminals accessing ransomware-as-a-service. The concept of public-key based data kidnapping and subsequent extortion was introduced in 1996. Since then, variants of ransomware emerged with different cryptosystems and larger key sizes, the underlying techniques remained same. Though there are works in literature which proposes a generic framework to detect the crypto ransomwares, we present a two step unsupervised detection tool which when suspects a process activity to be malicious, issues an alarm for further analysis to be carried in the second step and detects it with minimal traces. The two step detection framework- RAPPER uses Artificial Neural Network and Fast Fourier Transformation to develop a highly accurate, fast and reliable solution to ransomware detection using minimal trace points. We also introduce a special detection module for successful identification of disk encryption processes from potential ransomware operations, both having similar characteristics but with a different objective. We provide a comprehensive solution to tackle almost all scenarios (standard benchmark, disk encryption and regular high computational processes) pertaining to the crypto ransomware in light of software security."},{"title":"RAPPER: Ransomware Prevention via Performance Counters","subtitle":"Kangacrypt 2018","date":"Dec 2018"}]

name: Dinesh Goel
position: Co-Founder & CEO @ Robylon, Automating Customer Support using AI | Ex-founder, Aasaanjobs
about:
👋 I understand tech. I love solving problems & building companies.

I have 12+ years of experience building new age tech companies from scratch. Currently I'm on my 3rd venture.

Previously, I built Oneworldnation - a gaming platform built on blockchain. We launched 7 games and scaled to $2 mil ARR in a little less than 18 months. However, we decided to shut it down after an unfavorable change in the tax laws in India.

Before that, I built Aasaanjobs - an entry level hiring platform in India. We scaled it to ~$50 mil ARR and sold it to OLX, in a little less than 4 years. We worked with 50+ enterprises and over 400 mid-market companies in India, helping them hire ~40,000 people every year.

Currently, I am building Robylon where we help companies automate customer support using AI, across all 4 channels - Tickets, Chats, Social and Voice. Our solutions helps companies:

1. Automate >80% of customer queries
2. Improve Resolution times by >90%
3. Reduce costs by >30%

My Twitter: https://twitter.com/meetdineshgoel

--------------------------------------------------

🚀 I specifically enjoy discussions around these domains:

Automation
All things AI
Customer Support & Customer Experience
Recruitment
Blockchain & Cryptocurrency

name: Dr. Soumen Rej
position: Assistant Professor-Economics & IB at UPES
about: Dr. Soumen Rej, currently working as Assistant Professor in School of Business, UPES and defended Ph.D. thesis at the Vinod Gupta School of Management, Indian Institute of Technology Kharagpur, earned B.Tech in Electrical Engineering and M.Tech in Industrial Engineering and Management from West Bengal University of Technology (India), ranking second in his class to receive the Silver Medal from the University. He has also worked as a Research Fellow at Central Power Research Institute, Government of India. His research interests include Economics of Climate Change, Energy Policy, Energy Economics, advanced econometrics methods and Sustainability. He has the software proficiency of Python (advanced level), EVIEWS(advanced level), STATA(advanced level), R(beginner level), SPSS(beginner level). He also knows different MCDM techniques (TOPSIS, MTOPSIS, AHP, Fuzzy TOPSIS).

name: Suman Kumar
position: SWE @Deutsche Bank, Berlin 🇩🇪 || Former SDE intern @ Societe Generale, LetsTransport || IM+MNC+AI @IIT Kharagpur'23
about:
A graduate of IIT Kharagpur(Batch of 2023) with major in Industrial and Systems Engineering, minor in Mathematics and Computing and Micro Specialization in Artificial Intelligence and Applications. Currently, working as an Associate Software Engineer at Deutsche Bank, Berlin. I had a great internship experience at Societe Generale where I improved my skills in Machine Learning and Deep Learning. Before that, I had a fulfilling internship at LetsTransport where I worked on various projects related to backend development.
I like taking initiatives and am a hardworking person who is ready to put as much efforts needed to bring about a change.

name: Vatsal Gupta
position: Building FlexiLoans | Ex- Houlihan Lokey | IIT Kharagpur
about:
Growing up, I would dismantle every toy and gadget at sight in an attempt to understand how and why they work the way they do and try to rebuild them to full functionality. Just like everything in life, I succeeded at some and lost others. My broken toys were not enough to stop me, rather, I approached my next "experiment" with lessons from the failed ones to ensure success. I would attribute my greatest wins to my extremely inquisitive nature which enables me to understand what exists and opportunities to reinvent and recreate.

Greetings! I'm Vatsal Gupta, proud to be a part of the Founder's Office at FlexiLoans, where we're revolutionizing access to capital for businesses.

As a key player within the Founder's Office, my mission is to drive innovation, strategy, and execution to propel FlexiLoans forward in our mission to empower entrepreneurs and businesses with flexible financing solutions.

With a background in Financial Engineering from IIT Kharagpur, I bring a unique blend of Finance and statistics to the table, ensuring that FlexiLoans remains at the forefront of the fintech industry.

I thrive on collaboration and innovation, and I'm always eager to connect with fellow professionals, entrepreneurs, and thought leaders who share our passion for driving positive change.

publications: [{"title":"How Many Stocks for Maximizing Risk-Adjusted Return? Perspective from Indian Stock Market","subtitle":"Journal of Insurance and Financial Management","description":"Portfolio managers and investors alike continuously grapple with trying to outperform the benchmarks, while keeping in mind the right number of stocks in the portfolio for optimal diversification. Through our analysis of the Indian stock market, we show that by random selection of stocks, the odds of outperforming the index are very low. Instead, if investors incorporate the ‘quality’ factor in stock selection, the probability of outperforming the index improves substantially and is statistically significant - at around 5% outperformance per annum at 90% confidence.By incorporating the quality factor, they can own a fairly small basket of 15 to 25 stocks, which captures 90% of the benefit of owning the benchmark at 90% confidence and generates strong outperformance compared to the index. This is much lower than the 45 stocks required for reducing only the diversifiable risk by 90% with a 90% confidence, as the previous studies suggest. recommendations: ["James Fort “I had the pleasure of working with Nidhi as an intern on our team at Unity in the AI organization over the summer of 2020. Nidhi showed excellent initiative during her time here. She was able to take ownership of a very early stage project idea and drive it through to an actionable strategy for our organization in a new space. She was able to quickly come up to speed on a rapidly changing technology area, identify the relevant market sub-segments, work with stakeholders to source prospects, lead detailed technical discovery calls, and distill discovery learnings into an actionable strategy that she presented quite effectively at the VP level. I was impressed by her ability to both define this new customer segment and understand how our core technologies help in this area in such a short timeframe. I highly recommend her as a product manager in a technical space and believe that she has very high potential to grow as she progresses through her career.”","Kevin Saito “Had the pleasure of managing Nidhi during her internship at Unity. During her time here she had to quickly ramp up on the nature of B2B customer discovery and pull together a research project to help us identify whether we should enter an adjacent market segment. After a considerable amount of work her final project was very well received by our SVP and was deemed \"excellent\" and will likely lead to a change in our plans.”"]

name: Hritaban Ghosh
position: Data Analyst Intern in Global Decision Sciences - Artificial Intelligence L&G at American Express (May-July 2023) | 5th Year CSE - CG: 9.55 | IIT Kharagpur
about:
I am a Computer Science and Engineering Student pursuing my Dual Degree (B.Tech + M.Tech) at the Indian Institute of Technology, Kharagpur.

My passion for Machine Learning, Deep Learning, and Computer Vision is what has me gravitating towards making it my forever goal.

I have worked as a Data Science and Business Analytics Intern at The Sparks Foundation, where I had completed tasks while learning new tools such as Tableau and PowerBI. I went out of my way, and completed tasks from the domain of Computer Vision and the Internet Of Things wherein I had modeled an Object Detector and a Color Detector. I had self-learning experience with OpenCV and other libraries.

I am a quick learner and can take up new skills on the go. I have had experience in building ML models and Neural Networks along with building an AI that plays Breakout.

Skills: Machine Learning, Deep Learning, Programming in C, C++, Java, and Python.

[{"title":"Data Analyst Intern at AI Labs","location":"Bengaluru, Karnataka, India","description":"I had a very amazing experience interning at American Express. I was part of the Artificial Intelligence Learning and Governance, a branch of the Global Decision Sciences Team at Amex. During my internship, I worked on two projects. I started out with “Amex Insights – Leveraging layout information for marketing creative evaluation” where in Graph Neural Networks were used to embed the creative for analysis. We were able to evaluate the creatives as a whole up to nearly 96% accuracy. Furthermore, the model was built in such a way which allows for certain node level explanations and comparisons. After nearly 3 weeks into the internship, I took up another project “Financial Statement Spreading – Extract and Store Metadata with Financial Statements” which entailed extraction of data about tabular data in financial statements. I wrote a Custom Date Parser that was able to correctly infer a valid partial or complete date from a text up to 92% accuracy. I also worked on extracting sub headings from the document albeit the accuracy could only reach 50% due to the difficulty in correctly identifying a sub heading from all other text.Thanks to the amazing team at Amex, I was able to manage my time in both projects and deliver substantial results in both.           The annual NSS camp was held from 28 November - 4 December. The activities were centered around Shyameshwarpur, and encompassed the villages of, Nachna and Sholadhar. Around 550 first year students participated in the camp. The camp was inaugurated by Prof. Somesh Kumar (Dean SA, IIT Kharagpur) who appreciated the work done by NSSin the past, and inspired the students to do their best. During the annual camp, NSS volunteers participated in the construction of a nearly 1 km long drain, designed to relieve water congestion during the monsoon. They also cleared a nearly 400 m long path, which was overgrown and impassable, and made it suitable for use by the villagers.

name: Pranay Raj
position: Decision Analytics Associate @ ZS | IIT Kharagpur
about:
At the heart of my professional journey lies a passion for leveraging data analytics to drive strategic decisions in healthcare. At ZS, my role as a Decision Analytics Associate centers on enhancing the impact of Medical Affairs for pharmaceutical giants. We've partnered with clients to establish robust KPIs, enabling visual insights into the efficacy of field initiatives through innovative dashboards.

My education in Aerospace Engineering from IIT Kharagpur has honed a meticulous analytical mindset, crucial in crafting data-driven strategies for our clients. Coupled with proficiency in Google Analytics and PPC advertising, this background ensures a comprehensive approach to problem-solving and strategy building, fostering effective cross-functional collaboration.
